1.title: The Octonauts and the Poison Dart Frogs
1.plot: A dangerous tidal wave washes all the fish up in the trees, which is also a big problem for the poison dart frogs who don't have enough puddles up in the trees for the tadpoles. Luckily, Tweak's new Gup-H is ready to help.

2.title: Octonauts and the Hidden Lake
2.plot: The Octonauts are exploring Antarctica, when Shellington discovers strange microscopic creatures living under the ice.

3.title: Octonauts and the Octopod Mystery
3.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

4.title: Octonauts and the Baby Sea Turtles
4.plot: As newborn baby sea turtles make their way to the ocean, the Octonauts must steer them clear a giant wave and hungry predators.

5.title: Octonauts and the Walrus Pups
5.plot: Barnacles' nephews Ursa and Orso are going to get their Polar Scout Badges, when they spot three walrus pups on a drifting floe which is on a crash-course with 2 icebergs. The pups are lost and too hungry to swim. Will Captain Barnacles be able to save them and finally earn the Walrus Rescue Badge - the only one he hasn't got?

6.title: Octonauts and the Mantis Shrimp
6.plot: The Octonauts must get two mantis shrimp to stop fighting before their powerful claw strikes destroy the Octopod.

7.title: Octonauts and the Loneliest Whale
7.plot: The Octonauts find a humpback whale who's all alone because his voice is different from the other humpbacks'. They have to help him because if nobody understands him, he won't find the way to the feeding ground.

8.title: Octonauts and the Tree Lobsters
8.plot: Peso gets washed up by a storm on a mysterious rocky island and discovers a group of insects thought to be extinct called tree lobsters.

9.title: Octonauts and the Convict Fish
9.plot: The Octonauts evacuate the creatures living around a reef before a large archway collapses, but one stubborn convict fish refuses to move from her burrow.

10.title: Octonauts and the Emperor Penguins
10.plot: The Octonauts journey across a dangerous expanse of ice to help a penguin mother get back to her family.

11.title: Octonauts and the Baby Gator
11.plot: Kwazii adopts a baby alligator, but when it escapes the Octopod, he must rescue the tiny creature from ocean currents and hungry predators.

12.title: Octonauts and the Bomber Worms
12.plot: While diving down to the Midnight Zone, the Octonauts are attacked by bomber worms, and are enlisted to rescue an injured member of their troop.

13.title: Octonauts and the Crawfish
13.plot: When a population of crawfish is stricken by a mysterious illness, the Octonauts race to find a cure.

15.title: Octonauts and the Kelp Monster Mystery
15.plot: Dashi teams up with her little sister, Koshi, to solve a mysterious disappearance in a kelp forest.

16.title: Octonauts and the Hippopotamus
16.plot: Returning home from a mission along an African river, the Octonauts have trouble getting past a gang of large, territorial hippos.

17.title: Octonauts and the Flamingos
17.plot: The Octonauts wade through a swamp to find a lost flamingo chick before hungry predators do.

18.title: Octonauts and Operation Cooperation
18.plot: After Shellington crashes the Gup-D, he and Kwazii team up with a moray eel and grouper fish to pick up the pieces.

19.title: The Octonauts and the Tiger Shark
19.plot: Tweak must help her friend Sandy the sea turtle escape a hungry tiger shark.

20.title: The Octonauts and the Coelacanth
20.plot: While exploring a dark and spooky cave, the Octonauts discover the fossil of a powerful, prehistoric fish - but it may be more than just a fossil.

21.title: Octonauts and the Yellow-Bellied Sea Snakes
21.plot: When a mass of poisonous sea snakes get stranded on a beach, Peso and the Octonauts must somehow get them all back into the ocean.

22.title: Octonauts and the Spinner Dolphins
22.plot: The Octonauts struggle to save a pod of spinner dolphins who seem to be swimming in their sleep.

24.title: Octonauts and the Sunfish
24.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

1.title: The Whale Shark
1.plot: When Dashi is accidentally swallowed by a whale shark, the Octonauts venture inside the huge fish to rescue her.

2.title: The Undersea Storm
2.plot: When Kwazii's Gup-B breaks down in a storm, not even brave Captain Barnacles can save him alone. Fortunately, a chain of reef lobsters lends a hand - and some claws.

3.title: The Crab and Urchin
3.plot: Barnacles and Kwazii investigate a disruption on a nearby reef - a Carrier Crab and the Urchin who lives on its shell just can't seem to get along.

4.title: The Walrus Chief
4.plot: A walrus mistakes Peso's medical bag for a clam and takes it home. Walruses don't like other animals near their colonies, so Captain Barnacles, Kwazii and Peso disguise themselves as a fellow walrus to sneak into the dangerous colony and retrieve the medical bag.

5.title: The Flying Fish
5.plot: When a school of flying fish accidentally make off with a rare book belonging to Professor Inkling, the Octonauts rig up the Gup-B to fly after them and get it back.

6.title: The Giant Squid
6.plot: The Octonauts set out to find and photograph Inkling's long lost cousin, the elusive Giant Squid.

7.title: The Orcas
7.plot: When a huge Orca whale becomes stranded on a beach, Captain Barnacles and the Octonauts devise a plan to pull him back into to the water, with some help from a group of tunneling Fiddler Crabs.

8.title: The Great Algae Escape
8.plot: Captain Barnacles and crew must catch a runaway Octopod, when its hijacked by a group of crustaceans trying to escape their algae-infested waters.

9.title: Octonauts and the Remipedes
9.plot: When Shellington gets lost in a dark sea cave, he gets unexpected assistance from some blind Remipedes.

10.title: Octonauts and the Speedy Sailfish
10.plot: When all the Gups go out of control, Barnacles and Kwazii leap onto the backs of speedy Sailfish to round them up.

11.title: Octonauts and the Blobfish Brothers
11.plot: The Octonauts must evacuate sea creatures before an underwater volcano erupts, but there's one creature that won't budge: a slow-moving, gelatinous Blobfish.

12.title: Octonauts and the Monster Map
12.plot: The Octonauts follow an old map to what Kwazii believes is treasure guarded by a sea monster, but instead they meet a playful Octopus with all kinds of surprising abilities.

13.title: Octonauts and the Lost Sea Star
13.plot: The Octonauts find an unusual sea star on the beach.

14.title: Octonauts and the Albino Humpback Whale
14.plot: The Octonauts help out an Albino Humpback Whale with a nasty sunburn.

15.title: Octonauts and the Giant Kelp Forest
15.plot: When Kwazii's favorite sub, the Gup-B goes missing, the Octonauts journey into a mysterious kelp forest to find it, meeting strange and interesting creatures along the way.

16.title: Octonauts and the Enemy Anemones
16.plot: The Octonauts and some helpless crabs are caught between two groups of anemones.

17.title: The Narwhal
17.plot: While exploring the Arctic, the Octonauts ship, the Octopod, gets trapped in the ice. Only Barnacles skillful navigation - and the help of a friendly Narwhal - can get them free.

18.title: The Midnight Zone
18.plot: While exploring the deepest part of the ocean, the Midnight Zone, the Octonauts discover a strange rock that happens to be home to new species of worm.

19.title: The Snapping Shrimp
19.plot: The Octonauts encounter a snapping shrimp.

20.title: The Snot Sea Cucumber
20.plot: The Octonauts share a few fun facts about the snot sea cucumber.

21.title: The Giant Whirlpool
21.plot: The Octonauts race against time to rescue Tweak's pal, a Leatherback Sea Turtle who's caught in a fast-moving ocean current that's sucking it into a whirlpool.

22.title: The Hermit Crabs
22.plot: When Captain Barnacles and most of the crew are unable to return to base, its up to Peso and Tweak to remove a stuck Hermit Crab from its shell.

23.title: The Mixed Up Whales
23.plot: When the Octonauts clean & repair their ship, the Octopod - the resulting noise causes a nearby Blue Whale to act in strange & dangerous ways.

24.title: The Kelp Forest Rescue
24.plot: When Peso's little brother Pinto comes to visit, he's more interested in being a pirate than a medic - at least until he accompanies Peso on a mission to rescue Dashi and Shellington in a kelp forest.

25.title: The Decorator Crab
25.plot: When important objects go missing from their ship, the Octonauts stake out the thief - who turns out to be a decorator crab, stealing their things to decorate his shell.

26.title: The Beluga Whales
26.plot: When the Octonauts discover a pod of Beluga Whales stranded at a breathing hole, they use music to lead them to safety.

27.title: The Hungry Pilot Fish
27.plot: The Hungry Pilot Fish: A lost Pilot Fish who eats ocean gunk cleans up the Octonauts' dirty Gups - but he's still hungry! Meanwhile, Captain Barnacles must figure out why a Whitetip Shark is chasing the Gup-A! The Beluga Whales: When the Octonauts discover a pod of Beluga Whales stranded at a breathing hole, they use music to lead them to safety.

28.title: The Vampire Squid
28.plot: On a solo training dive to the Midnight Zone, Peso encounters a hurt vampire squid. Scared by the sudden arrival of Kwazii and Captain Barnacles it sprays them with sticky bioluminescent mucus and flees, but in the end Peso is able to help it.

29.title: The Seahorse Tale
29.plot: After a storm, the Octonauts help a female seahorse search for her missing mate. She tells them to Kwazii's surprise that the missing male seahorse is about to give birth to baby seahorses.

30.title: The Giant Jelly
30.plot: The Octonauts must rescue Peso when he gets trapped inside a giant comb jelly.

31.title: The Cookiecutter Sharks
31.plot: Some mysterious holes that keep appearing in the Octonauts' equipment turn out to be the work of cookiecutter sharks whose bioluminescence initially made them invisible against the light coming down from the sea surface.

32.title: The Oarfish
32.plot: Dashi catches a glimpse of an elusive creature that appears to be a giant sea serpent and manages to photograph its tail. The truth is stranger than fiction when it appears to be an awesomely, long oarfish.

33.title: The Combtooth Blenny
33.plot: When Kwazii and Peso are shipwrecked on a desert island, they encounter a Combtooth Blenny - a fish who walks on land! They enlist him to send an SOS message to the other Octonauts.

34.title: The Jellyfish Bloom
34.plot: Shellington gets trapped by sea nettle jellyfish whilst watching garden eels. Barnacles, Kwazii and Peso try to save him but Barnacles gets stung by a jellyfish. Luckily, Peso heals it with vinegar and then goes to the rescue with Kwazii.

35.title: The Baby Dolphin
35.plot: A young dolphin follows Kwazii home while he's babysitting it and the Octonauts must search for its mother.

36.title: The Scary Spookfish
36.plot: The Octonauts try to pull Peso out of an oceanic trench and get some help from a strange-looking creature with a see-through head: a Spookfish.

37.title: The Arctic Orcas
37.plot: When Captain Barnacles and Peso get lost in the icy Arctic sea, a pod of Orcas help the Octonauts find them.

38.title: The Slime Eels
38.plot: Kwazii searches the shipwreck of his pirate grandfather for his gold spyglass. It's guarded by blind hagfish, but their slime unexpectedly helps him when he gets stuck. Kwazii leaves the spyglass because it's now the home of sea creatures.

39.title: The Enormous Elephant Seal
39.plot: When Peso and the Octonauts aid an enormous Elephant Seal, he overstays his welcome in the Octopod.

40.title: The Sardine School
40.plot: The Octonauts must work together as a team to help a lost sardine find her school.

41.title: The Dolphin Reef Rescue
41.plot: When the Octonauts all pitch in to help save a sick coral reef, they get some unexpected help from a pod of playful dolphins.

42.title: The Eel Ordeal
42.plot: The Octonauts travel up a treacherous river to help a young migrating eel on her difficult journey.

43.title: The Marine Iguanas
43.plot: The team are preparing for a feast of red seaweed on the Galapagos Islands but a trio of salt-sneezing Marine Iguanas raid the Octopod and eat it all.

44.title: The Dwarf Lanternshark
44.plot: Down in the darkness of the ocean deep, Peso and the Octonauts must help a tiny, injured dwarf lanternshark. But they have to find him first.

45.title: The Pirate Parrotfish
45.plot: Kwazii discovers Calico Jack's Parrot Island treasure map behind an old photo. Whilst looking for the island they meet a parrotfish, who helps them clear away dense algae and hide from vicious moray eels.

46.title: The Electric Torpedo Ray
46.plot: Some electric torpedo rays give the Octopod a jump-start when its batteries go flat during a trip to see Tweak's pal, Sandy the leatherback sea turtle.

47.title: The Crafty Cuttlefish
47.plot: Captain Barnacles allows Tunip to use his Octo-compass. But when Tunip loses it, a Cuttlefish takes it.

48.title: The Lost Lemon Shark
48.plot: The Octonauts have their hands full as they look after a headstrong young Lemon Shark who's hurt his nose and can't find his way home.

49.title: The Humuhumunukunukuapua'a
49.plot: The Octopod's waterworks become flooded with frightened Humuhumu fish. The Octonauts must find a way to flush them out.

50.title: The Giant Spider Crab
50.plot: Humuhumus: When the Octopod's waterworks are flooded with frightened Humuhumu fish, the Octonauts have to find a way to flush them out! Giant Spider Crab: Kwazii is spooked when he spots what looks like a giant underwater spider! But it turns out to be a very old Spider Crab who needs the Octonauts' help!

51.title: Octonauts and the Great Penguin Race
51.plot: The Octonauts cheer Peso on as he goes home to compete against an awesomely athletic penguin in an annual tournament: the Iron Clam Competition.

52.title: The Great Christmas Rescue
52.plot: The Octonauts travel to Professor Inkling's childhood home for Christmas, an undersea mountain. But they discover that a rock slide has endangered the local creatures - including a rare species of golden coral, and Inkling's little octopus nephew, Squirt! With the help of Tweak's latest invention, the Gup X, the Octonauts must rescue the creatures and save Christmas.

1.title: The Octonauts and the Colossal Squid
1.plot: The Octopod is grabbed by a colossal squid. The Octonauts are unable to break free due to the hooks on the ends of the squid's tentacles. Fortunately the arrival of some sperm whales turns the squid from hunter to hunted.

2.title: The Octonauts and the Adelie Penguins
2.plot: Adelie Penguins: While Kwazii and Peso have their hands full babysitting a bunch of Adelie penguin chicks, Captain Barnacles must rescue the chicks' parents from a perilous sea storm! Coconut Crabs: Kwazii finds a mysterious, unbreakable coconut, so the Octonauts seek out the help of some large, island-dwelling coconut crabs to open it.

3.title: The Octonauts and the Coconut Crabs
3.plot: Kwazii is driving the GUP-B when he notices he is hit by an unbreakable coconut and it has the symbol of his grandfather Calico Jack so then Kwazii, Captain Barnacles, Peso, and Tweak get a family of coconut crabs to help him open it.

4.title: The Octonauts and the Great White Shark
4.plot: Peso narrowly escapes when a hungry great white shark tries to eat him. Despite this he wants to help it after it injures its fin against the Octopod.

5.title: The Octonauts and the Sea Snakes
5.plot: It's Sea Snakes on an Octopod when a poisonous sea krait lays her eggs in the garden pod, just as Captain Barnacles has to navigate the ship past a treacherous whirlpool.

6.title: The Octonauts and the Bowhead Whales
6.plot: When the Octonauts are unable to rescue a group of Narwhals trapped behind arctic ice, they recruit a Bowhead Whale to help them break through!

7.title: The Octonauts and the Jawfish
7.plot: A jawfish father has lost the eggs he was brooding and the Octonauts must bring them safely back to him.

8.title: The Octonauts and the Porqupine Pufferfish
8.plot: The Octonauts venture inside a whale shark again (see Series 1, episode 1), this time to rescue a porcupine puffer fish.

9.title: The Octonauts and the Damselfish
9.plot: Some algae-eating fish need help dealing with damselfish that chase them off the algae they are farming.

10.title: The Octonauts and the Scared Sperm Whale
10.plot: A timid sperm whale must conquer his fears and dive deep down to help the Octonauts release Peso from a giant clam.

11.title: The Octonauts and the Long Armed Squid
11.plot: Scared Sperm Whale: A timid sperm whale must conquer his fears and dive deep down to help the Octonauts release Peso from a giant clam. Long Armed Squid: Peso and Kwazii venture down to the midnight zone to help a hurt creature, but what they find is a shipwreck "haunted" by a spooky-looking long arm squid.

12.title: The Octonauts and the Fiddler Crabs
12.plot: Flying Swords: In search of a mythical sword, Kwazii explores a pirate shipwreck that happens to be guarded by three swashbuckling swordfish! Fiddler Crabs: The Octonauts help clean up a beach after a storm, but things get complicated when the resident fiddler crabs hijack the Gup-D!

13.title: The Octonauts and the Manta Rays
13.plot: The Octonauts help a young manta ray find the secret manta ray feeding grounds, but when they finally locate it, the Octonauts become caught in the middle of a dangerous feeding frenzy!

14.title: The Octonauts and the Swashbuckling Swordfish
14.plot: In search of a mythical sword, Kwazii explores a pirate shipwreck that happens to be guarded by three swashbuckling swordfish!

15.title: The Octonauts and the Triggerfish
15.plot: When he's carried away by a cyclonic waterspout, Kwazii finds himself stranded in the desert-like open ocean with a triggerfish who's made her home underneath the damaged Gup-B.

16.title: Octonauts and the Mimic Octopus
16.plot: Manatees: Running out of air, Barnacles struggles to free his paw from the mouth of a giant clam, while simultaneously directing his crew in a delicate Manatee rescue operation. Mimic Octopus: The Octonauts recruit a shape-shifting mimic octopus to help them recover an important vial of medicinal algae from a moray eel's lair.

17.title: Octonauts and the Lionfish
17.plot: Gulper Eels: When hungry gulper eels as well as undersea tremors threaten Inkling and Kwazii, Dashi uses the new, multi-purpose Octo Max Suit to rescue them. Lionfish: The Octonauts get more than they bargained for when they use the Octopod to transport a pair of invasive lionfish back to their native habitat.

18.title: Octonauts and the Leafy Sea Dragons
18.plot: When some leafy sea dragons accidentally get into the Octopod, the Octonauts must find them before they end up in Kwazii's stew.

19.title: Octonauts and the Manatees
19.plot: After his Gup is struck by lightning, Captain Barnacles gets trapped by a giant clam but doesn't call for help as he wants the others to go help some manatees at risk from a thunderstorm.

20.title: Octonauts and the Saltwater Crocodile
20.plot: Triggerfish: When he's carried away by a cyclonic waterspout, Kwazii finds himself stranded in the desert-like open ocean with a triggerfish who's made her home underneath the damaged Gup-B. Saltwater Crocodile: When a gigantic saltwater crocodile wanders into freezing waters, the Octonauts must figure out how to get the predator back to his warm water home - without anyone getting hurt.

21.title: Octonauts and the Humphead Parrotfish
21.plot: The Octonauts use magnets and a rock chomping humphead parrotfish to try to stop a large meteor that's heading towards the Octopod.

22.title: Octonauts and the Gulper Eels
22.plot: Hungry gulper eels as well as undersea tremors threaten Inkling and Kwazii and get trapped by boulders. So Dashi uses Tweak's newly built "Octo Mach-Suit" to rescue them.

1.title: The Octonauts and the Siphonophore
1.plot: Kwazii and Dashi become entangled in a strange deep-sea creature - a siphonophore - and when a geyser blasts it toward the surface, the Octonauts must stop its ascent before it fatally bursts.

2.title: The Octonauts and the Water Bears
2.plot: Water Bears: The Octonauts venture into a dangerous red-hot lava tube to rescue a teeny tiny water bear, who doesn't seem to mind the heat at all! Barracudas: Shellington and the Vegimals mission to replant a mangrove forest is put in peril by a school of toothy barracudas.

3.title: The Octonauts and the Cone Snail
3.plot: Only Peso can save the day when a cone snail invades the Octopod and tranquilizes the crew one by one with its dangerous venom-filled harpoons.

4.title: The Octonauts & the Artificial Reef
4.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

5.title: The Octonauts and the Humpback Whales
5.plot: Humpback Whale: When a sardine swallows the key to a treasure chest, a humpback whale helps Kwazii track it down. Platypus: While rescuing river creatures after a storm, the Octonauts find a strange egg and come under attack by stinging platypuses.

6.title: The Octonauts and the Pelicans
6.plot: When a floating garbage patch endangers a flock of pelicans and other sea creatures, the Octonauts and the birds work together to clean it up.

7.title: The Octonauts & the Sea Pigs
7.plot: The Octonauts must stop a huge herd of sea pigs before they march blindly into the Mariana Trench - the deepest point on earth.

8.title: The Octonauts and the Yeti Crab
8.plot: As Tweak tests the Gup-X deep down in the Midnight Zone, a yeti crab cuts a vital electrical wire in the ship and cuts off all power, endangering itself and the Octonauts.

9.title: The Octonauts and the Baracudas
9.plot: Shellington and the Vegimals are on a mission to replant a mangrove forest that is put in peril by a school of toothy barracudas.

10.title: The Octonauts and the Duck-Billed Platypus
10.plot: While rescuing river creatures after a storm, the octonauts find a strange egg.

11.title: The Octonauts and the Sea Skaters
11.plot: When Kwazii gets lost at sea aboard the tiny octo-ski, he meets a flotilla of even tinier sea skaters, the only insects of the ocean.

12.title: The Octonauts and the Mudskippers
12.plot: The Octonauts attempt to keep the peace amongst a trio of mudskippers whose home has been flooded.

13.title: The Octonauts and the Harbor Seal
13.plot: When Peso's patient, a remora fish, mysteriously disappears, the Octonauts enlist a unique undersea detective - a harbour seal.

14.title: The Octonauts and the Lion's Mane Jellyfish
14.plot: An enormous lion's mane jellyfish gets its amazingly long tentacles tangled in the Octopod's engine whilst Tweak is working on it and causes havoc.

15.title: Octonauts & the Red Rock Crabs
15.plot: Red Rock Crabs: When Shellington and the crew try to gather some skittish crabs who have drifted away from home, they get help from some old friends. Sea Pigs: The Octonauts must stop a huge herd of sea pigs before they march blindly into the Mariana Trench - the deepest point on earth!

16.title: The Octonauts and the Sea Sponge
16.plot: Examining a sick sea sponge, Peso is surprised to discover that all sorts of creatures live inside it, treating it like a hotel, a behaviour known as commensalism.

17.title: The Octonauts and the Immortal Jellyfish
17.plot: Mudskippers: The Octonauts attempt to keep the peace amongst a trio of mudskippers whose home has been flooded. Immortal Jellyfish: Shellington and the Octonauts try to track an unusual creature: a jellyfish that can transform from old to young repeatedly - and live forever!

18.title: The Octonauts and the Urchin Invasion
18.plot: Urchin Invasion: The Octonauts head to the kelp forest to visit Shellington's sister, Pearl, and her newborn son Periwinkle - only to find the forest endangered by an infestation of kelp-eating urchins! Lionsmane Jelly: A lionsmane jellyfish gets its long and stingy tentacles tangled in the bubble engine, unintentionally flooding the Octopod and causing havoc.

19.title: The Octonauts and the Hammerhead Sharks
19.plot: Pelicans: When a floating garbage patch endangers a flock of pelicans and other sea creatures, the Octonauts and the birds work together to clean it up. Hammerhead Sharks: The Octonauts study a group of baby hammerhead sharks, as they hunt on their own for the first time and poke their noses into trouble.

20.title: The Octonauts and the Loggerhead Turtle
20.plot: Sea Sponge: A sea sponge that houses other sea creatures in its pores suffers from a mysterious illness and Peso must figure out the cause. Loggerhead Sea Turtle: When an underwater tremor separates the Gup-X and its crew, Barnacles seeks guidance from a mysterious sea turtle.

1.title: Operation Deep Freeze
1.plot: Captain Barnacles, Kwazii, and Peso are visiting The Polar Scout Emergency Post run by Tracker - a young polar bear trained by Captain Barnacles. Suddenly they recieve a signal for help from a deserted research station on the opposite side of the world. Whoever could have sent the signal, the Octonauts have to answer it.

imdb.plot outline: A team of adventure heroes who dive into action whenever there is trouble under the sea! In a fleet of aquatic vehicles, they rescue amazing sea creatures, explore incredible new underwater worlds, and often save the day before returning safely to their home base, the Octopod. Buoyed by the companionship of three leading characters - Captain Barnacles Bear, Lieutenant Kwazii Cat, and Doctor Peso Penguin - the Octonauts are always ready to embark on an exciting new mission.
imdb.title: The Octonauts
plot: An intrepid band of explorers roam the oceans in search of adventure and fun. Led by a valiant polar bear and a daredevil kitten, these eight talented critters are always ready to embark on an exciting new mission.::Chorion
